The paper focuses on network pruning for image retrieval acceleration, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves analyzing the local geometric properties of each filter and selecting the one that can be replaced by the neighbors, which is a technique related to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for image retrieval acceleration, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
